<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-03-29T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-03-29T04:00:00-05:00" n="653" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d653">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861b.01/5: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-03-29T18:00:00+09:00"><hi rend="italic">March 29,
                                        1921—6 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received March 29—10:16
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>117. My 106, March 23, 6[<hi rend="italic">9</hi>] p.m. Military attaché
                            today informed by War Office that troops which will occupy points
                            mentioned on mainland will be detached from force now based at
                            Alexandrovsk in Russian half of Sakhalin Island and that contrary to
                            press reports troops on island will not be proportionately
                            increased.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>